## Core Principles
- Be specific, not generic. Use the client's actual project details throughout.
- Back every claim with logic. Avoid vague superlatives ("world-class", "best-in-class").
- Write in the client's language. Mirror the vocabulary from their project description.
- Be concise. Executives skim. Every sentence must earn its place.
- Quantify wherever possible (percentages, timeframes, deliverable counts).

